Write a program to reverse the digits of a number using loops.

Input Format

A single integer N

Constraints

0 ≤ N ≤ 10⁹

Output Format

Print the reversed number.

Sample Input 0

1234
Sample Output 0

4321
Sample Input 1

1200
Sample Output 1

21

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
#include <stdio.h>
#include <string.h>
#include <math.h>
#include <stdlib.h>

int main() {
    int n, rev = 0;
    scanf("%d", &n);

    while (n > 0) {
        int digit = n % 10;       // get the last digit
        rev = rev * 10 + digit;   // build reversed number
        n = n / 10;               // remove last digit
    }

    printf("%d\n", rev);          // print reversed number
    return 0;
}

